abstract: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y., Dec. 10.--The case of the people against Theodore H. Boyce, who shot Frederick W. abstract: HOPKINSVILLE, Ky., Dec. 29.--In a drunken brawl last night Capt. A.R. Perkins shot Col. L.A. Syphert, an ex-army officer and prominent lawyer. Both men were considerably under the influence of liquor. A dispute arose, when Syphert knocked Perkins down, whereupon the latter drew his pistol and fired, the bullet penetrating the thigh of Syphert, producing a painful wound. Perkins was held to ball in $1,000.
